					.content
						b Lorenzo
						| , originally from Italy, moved to South Carolina while in middle school. After overcoming the challenge of learning a new language in a foreign place, he joined his school's debate team and Youth in Government program to pursue his interest in politics and economics. He discovered his passion for finance and computer science after taking a myriad of online college courses at the height of the MOOCs boom in 2012. After graduating high school last May and advancing his coding skills at a local accellerator, Lorenzo moved to Palo Alto to work on Alpha-Sci full time. He is now being considered for the 2015 Thiel Fellowship. 
						hr
					.bottom
						p Lorenzo Barberis Canonico
				.contact-holder
					contact-image-holder
						img(src="assets/dan.png" alt="Dan's pic").img-circle.img-responsive
					h3.text-center Founder and Chief Technology Officer
					hr 
					.content
						b Dan
						|  is a software developer from Indiana. Initially an electrical engineer pursuing a PhD in material science, Dan discovered his true passion lied in software development, and thus embarked in an odyssey that would eventually land him in Greenville, South Carolina. By chance, he met Lorenzo at a local StartUp Weekend conference and they immediately connected over their passion for finance and programming. Dan has also recently become a father, which has brought him great joy and satisfaction. When he is not outputing amazing code or taking care of his wife and daughter, Dan enjoys watching Mad Men. 
					hr
					.bottom
						p Dan Shapiro
				.contact-holder
					contact-image-holder
						img(src="assets/jesus.png" alt="Jesus's pic").img-circle.img-responsive
					h3.text-center Chief Product Officer
					hr 
					.content
						b Jesus
						|  , originally from Mexico, moved to South Caroline while in high school. Jesus and Lorenzo met while representing South Carolina at the national conference for Youth in Government, and they instantly connected through they shared love of math and programming and more importantly through their shared belief in the American Dream. A programming prodigy since elementary school, Jesus has applied his talent in all of his many interests, ranging from robotics to economics. When is not changing the world through his code, Jesus spends his time taking online college courses and running cross country.  
					hr
					.bottom
